<paragraph blockId="34.[151,610,1120,1179]" box="[151,384,1154,1179]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">(Figs. 13.4 and 26.3)</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1226,1395]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Caatinga endemic species. This species is recorded only to the type-locality, Alagoado village, municipality of Casa Nova, state of Bahia. This is a lowland locality (ca. 
<quantity box="[843,918,1263,1287]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" unit="m" value="400.0">400 m</quantity>
elevation) on the western banks of the São Francisco river channel. It was recorded only in herbaceous and bushy caatinga with dunes and sandy soils (
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues" box="[158,345,1334,1359]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Rodrigues, M. T. (1992) Herpetofauna das dunas interiores do Rio Sao Francisco: Bahia: Brasil. V. Duas novas especies de Apostolepis (Ophidia, Colubridae). Memorias do Instituto Butantan, 54, 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1992">
Rodrigues 
<number box="[285,345,1335,1359]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It has fossorial and psammophylous habits, is diurnal and nocturnal, and feeds on elongated vertebrates (
<bibRefCitation author="Rodrigues" box="[288,472,1370,1395]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" refString="Rodrigues, M. T. (1992) Herpetofauna das dunas interiores do Rio Sao Francisco: Bahia: Brasil. V. Duas novas especies de Apostolepis (Ophidia, Colubridae). Memorias do Instituto Butantan, 54, 53 - 59." type="journal article" year="1992">
Rodrigues 
<number box="[412,472,1371,1395]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
